entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: hi i am ellie thanks for coming in today i was created to talk to people in a safe and secure environment i am not a therapist but i am here to learn about people and would love to learn about you i will ask a few questions to get us started and please feel free to tell me anything your answers are totally confidential are you ok with this

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay so how are you doing today

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am doing pretty well i have some stressful circstances going on but right now i am i am engaged

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good where are you from originally

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am from minnesota

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: really

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: hm i can not think of i can not think of one

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about your relationship with your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i have been married for it will be twenty four years in july

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: wow

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: which is a couple of months and my wife and i have not been sleeping in the same bed for about three years and but we have a a very high achieving daughter who is going to graduate from high school this this spring and she is just a gotten accepted at a college that she wants to go to with a very nice scholarship

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you find it easy to be a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah well my daughter is been very low maintainance for me perhaps more so for my wife but she is always been an excellent child

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah what is the hardest thing about being a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well the financial responsibility it wanting to make sure that your child has everything that her peers have and not wanting her to not have the same as her friends

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: and she has very wealthy friends so that is i am not a a gifted money maker and so it is a it is a a struggle but we we we keep on keep up

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh a couple of different one preacher whose church i attended for about twenty years until he died was very influential and also another spiritual guru that sort of put me on a path to breaking patterns of behavior that were kind of dictated by my upbringing

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: like what

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh just well instead of working for somebody else being able to start a business and and be in business for yourself and and to you know not be dependent on just one source of income

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh meeting one particular woman when i first got out here

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i i self medicate to go to sleep which i probably do not have to do but i about half the nights i i wake up much earlier than i would like to

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh usually just mostly to have to go to the bathroom

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i i i cope pretty well i i guess i am just not quite as functional as i would like to be there are a couple of nights a week when i work until two o clock from in the morning and do not get to bed until three and and then i normally if i i i need seven hours if i only get five or six then i am you know sluggish and

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: very anxious

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i have big i have bills to pay and not a lot of income coming in

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah it is cause i do not like to fall behind and i feel like i am worried about losing ground and the stakes are are high and so it is an uncomfortable position

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am a classic depressive and yeah i guess i have i i guess i have i see i do see a therapist and though the therapist i am seeing now is not trying to prescribe drugs or medications and previous ones have

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: probably six years ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well my wife kind of pushed me into it she thought it was a way of i think getting help finding work and it is not as it is just good enjoyed having someone to talk to

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good did you think you had a problem before you found out

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: not really yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what were your symptoms

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh just kind of not wanting to face the day just kind of wanting to just kind of a weariness with the struggle and just i displeasure with my life

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: they are what

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: aw that is so good to hear

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: is there anything you regret

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: hm no except meeting that one woman

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what advice would you give to yourself ten or twenty years ago

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not know probably try a little harder you know i had started this business around that time and it was it was just it was difficult but we were successful at it and i guess i could have gotten it rolling even more so that it would not be so dead today

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me how you spend your ideal weekend

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh getting out of town going going away when when which is rarely possible but yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you most proud of in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well my daughter is a great source of pride and the fact that i have been pretty successful in my endeavors and now i am just going for the the big the big apple and and i hope to be successful there too
